The Kaduna State government has confirmed fifteen new cases of COVID-19 in seven communities in the State. The communities are Zaria, Sabon Gari, Kaduna North, Kaduna South, Giwa, Chikun and Jema’a. It also stated that six COVID-19 patients are due for discharge. “Covid-19 Update: Six patients are due for discharge,” the government tweeted on its verified Twitter handle on Friday night. “15 new cases have been recorded, 4 in Zaria, 5 in Sabon Gari, 2 in Kaduna North and one each in Kaduna South, Giwa, Chikun and the first case in Jema’a,” it added.